coming from the CAPM.

54
00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:07.070
Now a related idea is

55
00:02:07.070 --> 00:02:09.335
something called
the Gordon Growth Model.

56
00:02:09.335 --> 00:02:11.060
The Gordon Growth Model is

57
00:02:11.060 --> 00:02:13.430
a benchmark method for
value and companies.

58
00:02:13.430 --> 00:02:15.080
What it does is it values

59
00:02:15.080 --> 00:02:17.975
any asset based on
its cash flows,

60
00:02:17.975 --> 00:02:19.370
and you can connect it with

61
00:02:19.370 --> 00:02:22.145
the capital asset pricing model
but you don't need to.

62
00:02:22.145 --> 00:02:24.680
So one idea is that
perhaps one could value

63
00:02:24.680 --> 00:02:27.170
cryptocurrency using
the Gordon Growth Model,

64
00:02:27.170 --> 00:02:29.890
and then you could decide is
Crypto over or under-valued.

65
00:02:29.890 --> 00:02:32.780
However, the Gordon Growth
Model values companies based

66
00:02:32.780 --> 00:02:34.010
